放不下中文会话 (Can’t Let Go Of Chinese) Ep. 27

[#放不下中文会话#] 放不下杯诗朗诵大会(上)

#EvenThoughChineseConvoIsLateButIt’sHere# #WhenKoiOpenItsMouthLuckWillComeToYou#

[Video]:
TH: Everyone, Spring is here. We sang《Spring Day》for you guys last winter, this time we’ve prepared a poem* about Spring.
YG: That’s right. Let’s start.
TH: In Spring one sleeps, unaware of dawn;
YG: One heard the sound of crowing birds everywhere.
TH: In the night came the sound of wind and rain;
YG: Will one know how many flowers fell?
YG: Ok everyone, hope you will be able to overcome the Spring fatigue and welcome the Spring of your life.
TH: But hyung looks a little bit fatigue too.
TH: Goodbye.

*(T/N: This poem is called “Spring Dawn” by the Tang dynasty Chinese poet Meng Haoran (孟浩然))
